article.headline: Maine 62, Stony Brook 56
article.story: ORONO, Maine (AP) -- Ernest Turner led four players in double figures with 17 points Wednesday as Maine held off several comebacks in a 62-56 victory over Stony Brook. Jon Sheets added 13 points, Philippe Tchekane Bofia 12 and 10 rebounds and Olli Ahveniemi 10 points, 11 rebounds and four blocks for Maine (8-11, 3-5 America East). Down 14-12 early in the first half, Maine used an 11-0 run highlighted by three consecutive baskets from Bofia to take command, 23-14. Stony Brook (3-15, 1-7 America East) answered with a 13-4 run to even the score and the two teams remained tied at the half, 31-31. Maine opened the second half with an 14-4 run to open its largest lead of the game, 45-35. Stony Brook responded with an 11-3 run to chip Maine's lead at just two points, but never got any closer. Maine held off a late run by hitting 8-11 free throws in the final two minutes. Bobby Santiago led Stony Brook with 16 points. Solomon Bamiro added 11 and 12 rebounds.
